# Firebase & Firestore

## Initialisation
- Import from `src/firebase/initFirebase.js`: `db`, `firebaseAuth`, `analytics`, `logAnalyticsEvent`
- Never initialise Firebase elsewhere; use shared instances

## Firestore Collections
- `Users` – user profiles (email, admin, developer, isActive, role, streak, etc.)
- `SystemSettings/toolConfig` – tool groups and links (see Tool Config Schema)

## Tool Config (SystemSettings/toolConfig)
- `groups`: array of `{ id, label, order, tools: [...] }`
- Each tool: `id`, `type` (internal|external), `path`|`url`, `label`, `icon`, `color`, `enabled`, `inDevelopment`, `allowedRoles`, `openInNewTab` (external)
- Legacy: flat `tools` array is auto-migrated to a single "Tools" group

## User Document Schema (Users/{uid})
- `email`, `firstName`, `lastName`, `admin`, `developer`, `isActive`, `role`, `userUID`
- `createdAt`, `lastLogin`, `streak` (ISO strings / numbers)

## User Utilities
- Use `ensureUserDoc(db, firebaseUser, overrides)` from `@/lib/userUtils` to create user doc on first login
- Use `updateLoginStreak(db, userId)` on each login

## Firestore Rules
- Current rules are permissive (dev only): `allow read, write: if request.auth != null`
- **Production**: Tighten to per-collection, per-role rules; validate field types and ownership
